Arthur Leonard Newbery (6 January 1905 – 17 December 1976) was an English cricketer. Newbery was a right-handed batsman. He was born at Battle, Sussex.
Newbery made his first-class debut for Sussex against Cambridge University in 1925. He made two further first-class appearances for Sussex in that season, against Nottinghamshire and Worcestershire. In his three first-class matches, he scored a total of 58 runs at an average of 11.60, with a high score of 50 not out, which he made on debut against Cambridge University.He died at Ightham, Kent on 17 December 1976.
